EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 262300 UTC
ON SATURDAY EVENING AND AT FIRST ON SUNDAY A LOW PRESSURE
CENTRE IN FITZROY WILL STEADILY FILL. THE SIBERIAN HIGH
PRESSURE WILL EXTEND A RIDGE ACROSS THE UK AT FIRST BUT
THIS WILL MOV NWARDS THROUGH SUNDAY AS A LOW PRESSURE
CENTRED IN THE LOW COUNTRIES DEEPENS TO 997 AND EXTENDS
TROUGHS OF LOW PRESSURE ACROSS THE N SEA AND UK. THE
RIDGE AXIS WILL BECOME ESTABLISHED FM ICELAND TO FITZROY
THROUGH MONDAY AND TUESDAY WITH THE LOW PRESSURE CENTRE
LOCATED NEAR THE DOVER STRAIT. WINDS WILL BE BROADLY NE
THROUGH SATURDAY EVENING. THROUGH SUNDAY WINDS WILL
BECOME STRG AT TIMES IN THE SERN N SEA INCLUDING FORTIES
AND FISHER LATER. ON MONDAY STRG N WINDS WILL EXTEND TO
ALL N SEA AREAS PERHAPS WITH N GALES IN HUMBER AND
THAMES AND IN CENTRAL AREAS OF THE N SEA LATER. WINDS
MAY BE STRG AT TIMES IN ALL SEA AREAS ON TUESDAY
